 on the origins of the book and by an account of the painting of Watkins's mural-sized canvas for the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library at Yale University. But the book's contents resist classification. Ninety-four of Watkins's paintings are reproduced, together with a catalogue containing his comments on individual pictures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Artists, Architects, Photographers.2bisacsh  aArchitecture.  aFine Art.  aGarden History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999z978311044252640uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151281941040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512819410423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781512819410.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  University of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK